# Harbor View appliance configuration.
#
# Copy to /etc/harbor-view/harbor-view.env (referenced by
# harbor-view-render.service's EnvironmentFile=). Unlike the project's
# own .env.example (for local development), this file's real,
# filled-in copy lives outside the git-tracked source tree entirely --
# /etc/harbor-view is not part of this repository -- so there is no
# risk of a real key ending up in version control. See
# docs/deployment.md.
#
# systemd EnvironmentFile syntax: plain KEY=value lines, no quoting,
# no "export", lines starting with # are comments.

# --- Vessel data source -----------------------------------------------
# "placeholder" (default) or "ais". Leave unset / commented out to get
# the placeholder fleet -- a fresh appliance should show something
# calm and complete out of the box, not an empty harbor because live
# data wasn't configured yet.
# HARBOR_VIEW_PROVIDER=placeholder

# Required only if HARBOR_VIEW_PROVIDER=ais. Get a free key at
# https://aisstream.io. See docs/sprint-004-notes.md.
# AISSTREAM_API_KEY=

# Optional, only relevant with HARBOR_VIEW_PROVIDER=ais -- see
# docs/sprint-004-notes.md for format and defaults.
# HARBOR_VIEW_AIS_BBOX=25.85,-80.30,26.45,-79.85
# HARBOR_VIEW_AIS_LISTEN_SECONDS=12

# --- Appliance lifecycle (Sprint 5) ------------------------------------
# Where the rendered PNG is written. Must match the path fed to feh in
# harbor-view-kiosk.sh -- the installer wires these together
# automatically; only change both together if you customize the install.
# HARBOR_VIEW_OUTPUT_PATH=/var/lib/harbor-view/harbor_view.png

# How often (seconds) to render a new frame. Brief specifies 60.
# HARBOR_VIEW_REFRESH_SECONDS=60

# Where the display process's PID is recorded, so the render loop can
# signal it to reload after each successful render. Must match
# harbor-view-kiosk.sh's PID_FILE.
# HARBOR_VIEW_DISPLAY_PID_FILE=/var/lib/harbor-view/feh.pid

# Python's logging level for the refresh loop (DEBUG/INFO/WARNING/
# ERROR). Logs go to journald either way -- see docs/deployment.md.
# HARBOR_VIEW_LOG_LEVEL=INFO
